51:  * <p>
52:  * A CDS is a financial instrument where the protection seller agrees to compensate
53:  * the protection buyer when the reference entity suffers a default.
54:  * The protection seller is paid premium regularly from the protection buyer until
55:  * the expiry of the CDS contract or the reference entity defaults before the expiry.
56:  */
